CLOSED-LOOP (Reuse, Repair, Refurbish, Remanufacture, Recycle): It means an extension of the utilization period of goods through the design of long-life goods; the introduction of service loops to extend an existing product’s life, including reuse of the product itself, repair, reconditioning/refurbishing and technical upgrading, and/or a  combination of these. The result of the reuse of goods is a slowdown of the flow of materials from production to recycling. This strategy: [Complies with regional and national regulations]

Its main objective is to guarantee the competitiveness of the economic sector in order to reduce the values and benefits sharing. This strategy: [Complies with regional and national regulations]

FINANCIAL INCENTIVES AND/OR SUPPORT AND FISCAL MEASURES: It can be three types of initiatives: 1) Financial incentives that can be considered monetary rewards to promote the take-back and recycling activities, in general, aimed at consumers. 2) Financial support, which refers to grants, subsidies, direct and Indirect investments, and public-private partnerships through which city governments can enable city development towards a circular economy. The funds may draw on existing budgets and revenues or be raised in addition and specifically to support circular economy initiatives.  3) Fiscal measures such as taxes, penalties, and charges, can help incentivise or discourage behaviours.  This strategy: [Complies with regional and national regulations]
